<TITLE> Two killed in Rangamati shooting </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Rangamati, Mar 2 (bdnews24.com)  Two members of UPDF died and a fishermen injured as unknown assailants opened fire on an auto-rickshaw at Jurachhari upazila town on Tuesday afternoon. The victims, members of United Peoples Democratic Front, Raju Chakma, 26 and Dempeda Chakma, 19, were shot as they headed towards Dhamai para of Bonjogichhara area in the upazila from the Chotpudi launch terminal in an auto-rickshaw around 5.30pm. A group of 5/6 assailants opened fire on the auto-rickshaw and killed the duo on spot. A local fisherman and passerby, Lakkhiraj Chakma, was injured in the shooting. He was admitted to the upazila health complex. UPDF's district coordinator Shanti Dev Chakma blamed the killing on Chittagong Hill Tracts Jonoshonghoti Samiti's Santu group. "The assassination was carried out when UPDF, through democratic movement, were struggling for the freedom of indigenous people in the hill areas", he said. He strongly criticised the killing and demanded arrest of those involved. However, Chittagong Hill Tracts Jonoshonghoti Samiti's central information and publicity secretary Mangal Kumar Chakma rejected the claims of its involvement, saying, "UPDF is placing the blame to cover their own misdeeds" . The district police super Masud-ul Hasan confirmed the deaths. bd
